abstract: Party leaders are cautioning candidates in the midterm elections not to campaign on impeachment, for fear of inciting conservatives to vote in defense of President Trump.
snippet: Party leaders are cautioning candidates in the midterm elections not to campaign on impeachment, for fear of inciting conservatives to vote in defense of President Trump.
lead_paragraph: MATTHEWS, N.C. — Democrats in Washington are wary of any talk about impeaching President Trump, but in this swing district in North Carolina, Janis Silverman is feeling no such constraints. A 72-year-old retired teacher, Ms. Silverman wrote to her congressman Tuesday to demand the House start impeachment proceedings.

abstract: President Recep Tayyip Erdogan appears to be going down the same ill-fated path that was taken by the failed authoritarian leaders of Venezuela and Zimbabwe.
snippet: President Recep Tayyip Erdogan appears to be going down the same ill-fated path that was taken by the failed authoritarian leaders of Venezuela and Zimbabwe.
lead_paragraph: Inflationary crises, like the one looming over Turkey, are bad news for any government, but they are especially dangerous for a certain subset of authoritarians: populist strongmen.

headline_main: What Is an Essence and Why Is It More Important Than Moisturizer?

abstract: Three friends of the president have quietly influenced decisions at the Department of Veterans Affairs, including the firing of the secretary. They seem to be growing bolder.
snippet: Three friends of the president have quietly influenced decisions at the Department of Veterans Affairs, including the firing of the secretary. They seem to be growing bolder.
lead_paragraph: A new secretary was sworn in at the Department of Veterans Affairs in late July, but the people actually in charge of the agency may not have changed, and they are not at the headquarters in Washington, but on the manicured grounds of Mar-a-Lago, President Trump’s West Palm Beach estate.

abstract: A reader wonders whether it’s appropriate to turn down play dates with children whose parents own firearms.
snippet: A reader wonders whether it’s appropriate to turn down play dates with children whose parents own firearms.
lead_paragraph: Our son will soon be old enough for independent play dates, where I drop him off with another family for an hour or two. My husband and I have a firm no-gun policy in our home (not even toy guns). I understand that other families may own guns legally, but I disagree with their decision from an ideological and safety standpoint. Accidents can always happen. I want to institute a policy: No playing at houses with guns. How can I ask other parents if they own guns? And how can I refuse play dates if they do? It’s not personal; it’s just our policy.

abstract: The party’s odds aren’t great, but they look better all the time.
snippet: The party’s odds aren’t great, but they look better all the time.
lead_paragraph: The chamber of Congress that Democrats are best positioned to wrest control of in the midterm elections is the House. That’s indisputable. But the lopsided focus on it — I plead guilty myself — sometimes creates the impression that taking the Senate is a pipe dream and lost cause. And that’s insane.

headline_main: Democrats, Do Not Give Up on the Senate
headline_print_headline: Democrats, Do Not Give Up On the Senate

abstract: The Republican leader is walking away. Don’t ask him about Trump anymore.
snippet: The Republican leader is walking away. Don’t ask him about Trump anymore.
lead_paragraph: Paul Ryan has a thing about punctuality and routine. They bring a sense of order to the chaos that he otherwise must try to maneuver through. We sat down at 9 a.m. sharp in the ornate offices of the speaker of the House at the United States Capitol. It was a Wednesday in late July, and Ryan had a packed morning, starting with an appearance on “Fox & Friends” and ending with a meeting at the White House with President Trump — if there is even a difference.

headline_main: This Is the Way Paul Ryan’s Speakership Ends

abstract: Ricky Strauss, a successful marketer, has been given oversight of original films and TV shows for Disney’s coming streaming service. Does he have what it takes?
snippet: Ricky Strauss, a successful marketer, has been given oversight of original films and TV shows for Disney’s coming streaming service. Does he have what it takes?
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Very little is known about Disneyflix, as some people in Hollywood are calling the Netflix-style streaming service that Disney plans to introduce late next year.

abstract: Yes, I have a single mom. Don’t panic.
snippet: Yes, I have a single mom. Don’t panic.
lead_paragraph: My freshman year in college I went on a date with an earnest boy from my dorm who had ears that stuck out when he grinned. He had been raised Catholic and gone to an all-boys school, and I was charmed by him. I was also generally enthusiastic about college dating, because I hadn’t done much of it. We sat flirting in a booth near the back of a club called Elevate, and everything went well until he broached the subject of my childhood.
